*FAT:	have we started yet ? 3985_5085
%mor:	aux|have-Fin-Ind-Pres-P1 pron|we-Prs-Nom-P1 verb|start-Part-Past-S adv|yet ?
%gra:	1|3|AUX 2|3|NSUBJ 3|0|ROOT 4|3|ADVMOD 5|3|PUNCT
@Comment:	Time is 0:06
@Situation:	MT is about 30 minutes long , with Mot , FAT , and Chi eating together; Chi asks questions implying that he remembers things from when the family lived in East Boston; parents are worried that he's <telling tales> and explain that it's okay to have an imagination but you have to tell people when you're telling a story; the boy who cried wolf is mentioned; also some talk about book reading , and rare words like twilight; negotiations about food; Chi agreed to eat chili , but then wouldn't; he says he thought it was meat chili , and parent's are scandalized <we don't eat meat!>; there's an extended discussion of how people are starving in Somalia; very middle class like interaction , typified by the father showing off his knowledge for the tape recorder
